State of Connecticut v. Floyd Williams (10327)

Dupont, C. J., Foti and Heiman, Js.

Argued April 29 decision released May 18, 1993 *915Auden Grogins, special public defender, for the appellant (defendant). Richard F. Jacobson, assistant state’s attorney, with whom, on the brief, were Donald A. Browne, state’s attorney, and Linda N. Howe, assistant state’s attorney, for the appellee (state). Per Curiam.

The judgment is affirmed.
